<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(24)">Lurtz, Servant of Isengard</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(39)">Troop of Uruk-hai</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(311)">Uruk Lieutenant</a> x2<br>
Uruk Captain x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(42)">Uruk Fighter</a> x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(856)">Uruk Warrior</a> x4<br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(25)">Lurtz&#39;s Battle Cry</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(31)">Saruman&#39;s Ambition</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(855)">Savagery to Match Their Numbers</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(36)">Spies of Saruman</a> x2<br>
Beyond the Height of Men x2    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> <b>Please read before reviewing</b><br>
<br>
I have seen many people attempt to make Balrog decks, and sighed at them, and so here is my attempt, and tests have shown it to be rather successful.<br>
<br>
First off, why Flame of Udun? If you use Flame of Udun, you have to use Moria, and as I will describe later on, Moria is not the way to complement Balrog deck. Yes, Moria complements, but only Balrog SWARM. Flame of Udun fits in a Moria Swarm deck, and Moria Swarm decks, my friend, are seen so much they&#39;re BORING. Try THIS.<br>
<br>
Durin&#39;s Bane is much more effective because you don&#39;t want a swarm. You want a big monster to kill 2 companions. Durin&#39;s Bane skipping of the archery phase is also amazing, meaning your opponent must fight him and with your support cards, you are simply going to rip his fellowship in half.<br>
<br>
So, 4 Whips and 4 Final Cry. No Balrog&#39;s Sword because it sucks. Whip + Final Cry does the job well enough. 4 for each so you draw them before Site 5, and with the card-draw power of the Fellowship with Elrond, Ottar, Gandalf and Celeborn, this is feasible. You will want to wait for him at Site 5 with Whip and multiple Final Cries. That makes the Balrog 18 Strength, enough to overwhelm anybody without possessions except Gandalf Friend of the Shirefolk. If he pushes up Boromir + Armor, discard the Armor with Whip and use Final Cry if needed. If he attempts to Stealth, kill him with Final Cry. All other companions, use Final Cry if needed (make sure you toss all your Final Cries at Site 5 even if you don&#39;t need it to kill)<br>
<br>
In all its tests, the fellowship has always left the Bridge with 2 companions gone.<br>
<br>
As for Whip and Final Cry, 4 of each can clog up your hand seriously after Site 5, and that&#39;s what the Fellowship is for. 2 Ottars and 2 Wizard is Never Late to draw Ottar quick, and he allows you to toss those Balrog goodies after Site 5 (or toss an extra Whip of Many Thongs before Site 5) for better card-draws. Gwemegil is also very huge. Use it often to get rid of Balrog goodies after Site 5 even if you don&#39;t need the strength-boost.<br>
<br>
As for which shadow to complement the nasty Balrog? Let&#39;s see...Moria would be plain stupid. We&#39;re not swarming, we&#39;re destroying the fellowship. Nazgul...they usually need Site 5 to release their hand and their high twilight costs don&#39;t agree with the Balrog&#39;s need for card economy either. Sauron...simply put, you cannot touch them much before Site 5 to weaken them for the Balrog, and Sauron simply cannot complement this type of deck. It leaves to Isengard beatdown, THE choice for the Balrog&#39;s assistants! With this deck, we are aiming for multiple wounds, and the Lurtz&#39;s Battle Cry-Saruman&#39;s Ambition is unbelievably damaging. Even without, their Damage +1 smiles well with the Balrog. Furthermore, Hollin can allow you to unleash the Uruks in time for the Balrog to make his grand entrance. With this in mind, the Uruks were designed with maximum wound-potency in mind. Battle Cry is a sure-fire way of getting rid of Boromir, Arwen and Legolas (and 2 can destroy Aragorn and Gandalf unawares). Savageries can cause an overwhelm from nowhere. Spies combats the irritating archers and Orophin. Fear not that you will not draw into the Isengard minions due to the card slots the Balrog occupies, tests with this deck have shown that playing 3 Uruks a turn is no problem at all.<br>
<br>
For the Fellowship, due to our requirement for Ottar and Gwemegil, Gandalf and Arwen are automatic choices. Elrond needs to heal Ottar. Arwen&#39;s only feasible choice for a starting companion is Greenleaf. Aragorn needs to heal Arwen. Celeborn complements Elrond. So here we go, a standard Ranger/Elf/Gandalf fellowship, with emphasis on getting Ottar and Gwemegil out for card advantage.<br>
<br>
Why Grey Pilgrim instead of Friend of the Shirefolk? Gandalf is used for his bag o&#39; tricks (Servant, Sleep etc) and Gandalf&#39;s Staff, not as a big guy to block minions.<br>
<br>
As for the sites, Pony requires no explanation. His Aragorn signet-heal is way too important. Trollshaw has to be one of the best neutral sites around. Rivendell Valley and no Rivendell Waterfall because no ARV in the deck. Hollin for the Uruks to wreak some damage as they will miss out in the Bridge. Galadriel&#39;s Glade because no ARV in the deck. Wilderland because I prefer to hurt my opponent than getting myself screwed. Shores as due to the lack of Thror&#39;s Map, you will always be playing this site. Slopes to reduce the twilight cost of Uruks.<br>
<br>
This deck may look a little strange due to its doubtful purpose but trust me, it works. The Balrog destroys 2 companions all the time and the Uruks almost always clean up everything. And even if the shadow fails, the Fellowship is more than capable of running to Site 9 with the Uruks slowing you down. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=22635"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=22635" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
